message.text:
#fromtheinbox

"CALCULATOR "

Last Saturday(9/13/2025) at the Mezzanine Floor ENB(3:00pm), a female student approach our table asking to borrow a calculator. I don't know maybe she forgot to bring hers or she doesn't have one. Regardless, I was once in that situation. I forgot to bring my calculator during my early years in TECH, to cut it short, someone was kind enough to lend me theirs and of course I thankfully returned it. I was able to relate with this female student so I lend her mine. She told us that she would be done by 4pm. We waited until 4:30 but no one came. I didn't received a message from her.

Calculator model: CASIO fx-991cw(black)

Disclaimer: I made this post not to spread hatred, don't bash her because we don't know her side of the story.

To ate girl: I hope you did well in your exam, I just want my calculator back please. Kindly message me at my email calmepotato@gmail.com. Thank you and God bless.

Last Saturday(9/13/2025) at the Mezzanine Floor ENB(3:00pm), a female student approach our table asking to borrow a calculator. I don't know maybe she forgot to bring hers or she doesn't have one. Regardless, I was once in that situation. I forgot to bring my calculator during my early years in TECH, to cut it short, someone was kind enough to lend me theirs and of course I thankfully returned it. I was able to relate with this female student so I lend her mine. She told us that she would be done by 4pm. We waited until 4:30 but no one came. I didn't received a message from her.

Calculator model: CASIO fx-991cw(black)

Disclaimer: I made this post not to spread hatred, don't bash her because we don't know her side of the story.

To ate girl: I hope you did well in your exam, I just want my calculator back please. Kindly message me at my email calmepotato@gmail.com. Thank you and God bless.
